In large organizations, the application portfolio is usually quite large.  While some applications are tightly coupled to a particular business function, many are platforms that enable and support many business value streams.

## Business Domain Jira Project
A business domain project typically will hold multiple specialty value streams. For these teams, the Epics reflect each Value Stream. which can then be broken down into Value Stages (Feature), Capability Enhancements (Stories) and then the specific tasks that need to be accomplished. From a Jira perspective, the Jira components will = Business Applications.

In this scenario, there are application teams that are tightly coupled with the business domain to collaboratively enhance the business value streams. These applications can then be associated with the appropriate user and enabling stories (ie Capability Enhancements).
## Application Team Jira Project
Let's look now at a centralized custom application development team that may support multiple business domains with specialized applications. Within this Jira project, the components are still aligned to business applications, but Epics and Features may be more aligned to software upgrades or managing the underlying technology stack to ensure that an application does not fall into some form of technical debt.

Overlaid on this will be the stories that come from Business Domain Jira projects.